So good! Such friendly service and really good food with fair prices. As close to Japan as you can get in Denver.
Absolutely my favorite place to study, best korroke in town.
One of my top places for quality Japanese food. Entered near eleven, it wasn't packed. Prices were average for the menu.
Japanese food and the setting here is above par. very filling. looking forward to returning with my relatives. the bill was fair i would say. menu is like a place in miami i enjoyed
japanese food and the scene here is excellent. Bring your appetite because portions are large.

Perfect if you know Japanese food! Tastes like any Mom n' Pop place you could find in a small town. Simple, affordable food. Team was very happy with tempura somen + upon, as well as negi ramen. Also, the nice lady upfront was very fine with talking to me in Japanese, and I really appreciated it!
japanese food, yeah, so delicious. Service is always excellent even when they have a full house. Prices were fair. Menu is like a place in San Francisco I loved.
One of my preferred locations for tasty Japanese food. Don't worry if it's busy, it is worth the wait. Will surely make a return trip. The bill was good for how much you get.
My fav place for Japanese food. certainly a top place in the area. it has a good interior. atmosphere is similar to a place in columbus i loved.

The staff was nice, but let’s talk food. Shumai cold. Tonkatsu broth and Soy based ramen very bland. Egg was soft boiled but cold and meat tasted a day old or so. Very disappointing and unhappy despite the high reviews - it’s like those reviews were just lies!
A top site for delicious japanese food. great place to meet and catch up with friends. i've had nothing but enjoyable experiences here and plan to keep visiting.
Amazing food
Tiny portions and high prices. Never again.

Great place for authentic Japanese food in a relaxed setting for a great price. Perfect for a quick lunch or casual dinner. Staff is very courteous and friendly. Food is well portioned and perfectly prepared. I had the Chasu ramen and …
Excellent and authentic.

Authentic japanese food. I receive excellent service every time. I visit them regularly. Thanks!!

Amazing hole in wall. Even with a bit of a shabby decore it's Japanese comfort food at its best. Please try the saba shio (salted and broiled macrel) they do it just right. Set meals are the way to go for an economical lunch. Polite staff, …

took around 45 minutes to get soup. every table had dishes on it and they must've been sitting there close to an hour since i was as well. my order came wrong anyway. 2 hours after leaving, i'm still starving. will be a loooong time before i consider coming back.
Closest thing to authentic Japanese you'll find in Denver. Real cold soba noodles and curry udon. Ramen is pretty good too but I go for the cold soba mostly.

I live in the building attached to the restaurant and waited two years to try it. Incredibly disappointed.

Food and service were great, environment was dated. Loved it tho.

Quiet, unassuming restaurant with top notch ramen.

Best Japanese food l have tasted in Denver. I tried many popular Japanese restaurants in Denver like Uncle, DOMO etc. but nothing taste as ‘real Japanese food’ as here. Probably because the food is made from Japanese staffs. 10/10 recommended. I do wish they open the restaurant longer tho.
Every top-tier ramen house I've ever been to has been small, unassuming, and hidden. Sakura House only serves to confirm this rule.  You want to be here.
Genuine Japanese food. Good experience！
Great service,  amazing food!

It’s a gem! Located in Sakura Square behind Pacific Mercantile, it has a home style cooked meal feeling and great flavor. I tried the gyoza, ramen (soy), and beer curry and it was all solid. For the price, flavor and service it’s an awesome find in the middle of Denver.
Always great Japanese food ..
We love the food every time we visit! Not fancy but the food is great. The chicken karage is great so are their udons.
We waited around on a Tuesday 15 minutes after opening. They never opened. A server walked by but didn't say a word. There was no sign saying they weren't offering business either.
Can't beat this Japanese place for the price but isn't anything special
It's great. Every time. The ramen is deep and the noodles are perfect. Apps are delicious as well. Home-y feel you cant go wrong at!
Yum, I'll be back!
Astonishing ramen !! Brought to great heights !!
Quite authentic and probably the best bang for your ramen buck in denver.

No frills menu that delivers excellent tastes for ramen and a few other Japanese dishes. They have many types of ramen to choose from with different broth bases and your choice of toppings. My gf was in the midst of a cold when we went and …
Amazing ramen! We were looking for a ramen shop and will be back many times over!
This place is delicious. The ramen is super flavorful. Nice clear broth that leaves a nice coat of flavor that lingers in your mouth. Great portions and a great filling meal.

Fantastic restaurant owned and operated by Japanese.  Food is absolutely incredible, not expensive, and prepared quickly.  Service: stellar.  Super friendly staff whose goal is to make your visit as pleasant as it can be.  I can't wait to get back up there to try more of their offerings!  Pictured is curry ramen...
Absolutely amazing food, great prices and a whole lot more. This spot is great for when you're craving some rainy day food and need a big bowl of comfort
Very good ramen!
The food was great but the service was a little slow otherwise a great visit. I highly recommend for everyone to try this restaurant!
Food tasted great however it took some time to get to us. Interior is a bit run down due to being an older restaurant.
Great restaurant. The wait time is worth it.
Excellent Japanese restaurant in Sakura Square. A lot of good options that satisfied my craving for the food I had in Japan.
Went here during the festival. Honestly, let down and I love Japanese food. Service was great but the food was mediocre. I hope it was just because they were too busy with the festival crowd.

I've been coming to Sakura House for some years now, and every single visit has been a five star experience. It's casual; the service is always super friendly; the food is very delicious; the portions are generous ... generous but not …

Most authentic Japanese home style cooking in CO. Sadly I hear whoever owns Sakura Square will be "renovating" it next year and running the few Japanese-owned businesses out. Pacific Mercantile and Sakura House will be gone. What a loss and lack of vision by the people doing this....
It's difficult to find good Japanese in Colorado, I think people are easily impressed with any kind of sushi and rate highly. This place is a staple. おかわり！
Always delicious, so hard to find good Japanese in Colorado. This one is a staple.
Super delicious and authentic Japanese. Clean, quiet and relaxing dining area in the sea of bustling downtown.

Absolutely loved it. Went on a date with my boyfriend and the food was delicious and personally thought decor was great. The service and staff were kind. Have only been once but hoping to go back a lot more.
Amazing and authentic food!
Legit Japanese fare in a comfortable and unassuming setting. Owners are very nice.
Introduced my friend to so authentic home cooking style Japanese cooking. That being said, he enjoyed it. I really this place is a great place to get your Japanese cooking fix.
Love the food!
Always great food!  Feels like one of the little neighborhood restaurants in Japan.

My mother, toddler, and I went here before Christmas and we were so happy about the food and atmosphere. The food was aaaaamazing, we couldn't get enough of it! The atmosphere is simple and laid back, which I personally love. They were very accommodating to my little one! Am going back today!

Hole in the wall Japanese restaurant. This place has excellent spicy ramen and is relatively cheap. The only downside of this place is that it is off the beaten path and is a little dingy... But this is also what makes this place awesome

Absolutely love this place. I come back whenever I can. Delicious food, very kind staff. Greeting and thanking in Japanese gives it the entire place a great atmosphere. Cute - quaint and delicious.

It's the same family that owned Genroku some years back, and the food is just as good. Easily the best ramen in Denver, and very friendly service. I just wish it had longer hours.

I have yet to be disappointed by anything I have tried here. Sakura House reminds me of my time living in Okinawa. Staff is very friendly and despite only the one woman taking orders she always does do with a smile no matter how busy it gets. I have brought many friends here and they have enjoyed their experience.
Sadly, no gluten-free options. But a great little hole in the wall. Feels like a good place that only the locals know about.
Had the udon and tempura. The broth was really good and the tempura, especially the shrimp tempura, was fried perfectly. Took a while to get our food but worth the wait.
Service is a little bit slow, environment is a bit rough around the edges, but the food more then makes up for it.
Tenshin rice bowl: omelet with crunchy veggies and filled with shrimp in a thick tasty sauce!
Awesome menu choices with friendly staff.
Went for lunch;not a huge bento box fan.

This is a realy great and authentic place to grab Japanese food. Love the Ramen there as well at the katsu and mabo tofu. Forgot my credit card, and they kept it safe for me. They are very friendly and reasonably priced. It is not too crowded for dinner, though they do get busy during M-F lunch.
friendly service, marginal ramen, nothing special dining environment
The Katsu Don was amazing. A great place to feel home and eat in central Denver.
The food is the emphasis and it's amazing! Katsu chicken was amazing and the Ramen was delicious. Definitely coming back here.

It's the closest I've felt to Tokyo since my trip there last year. And the prices are easily the best in town. Highly recommended.
An oasis in a desert of downtown dining. Among the best of Japanese eats in Denver.
It's the only real Japanese restaurant in downtown Denver. The portions, price, and food are all spot on. The decor might not be much, but that's not an issue for me.
